I know, you are tired of repeting the same command which generates almost the same output being almost imposible to discern between rounds.

This is the solution! You only have to download the bash script into /usr/bin/ directory or somewhere else and adding its path to the PATH variable.
Then you run it like: cleanline numberoflines string
for example: cleanline 10 @# will generate:

